# Reflection surfaces use git's built-in union merge driver so that
# concurrent merges combine both sides' appended lines instead of
# conflicting — no committed reflection can be silently dropped.
#
# Source of truth is the per-entry fragments in reflections/active/
# (one file per reflection, so they never collide); these rules protect
# the generated aggregate and the append-only annual archives.
#
# Scaffolded by /superpowers-init and /harness-init. Merge these lines
# into the project root .gitattributes.
REFLECTION_LOG.md merge=union
reflections/archive/*.md merge=union
